1879072112.name: Barrow-downs Hunter

1879072115.description: The folk of Bree-land hail your efforts to protect the roads from roving bandits.
1879072115.name: Watcher of Roads

1879072118.description: You've proven a match for the rotten hatred the trees of the Old Forest hold for the two-footed folk of Middle-earth.
1879072118.name: Root-hewer

1879072121.description: Who would ever have thought that Neekerbreekers could grow that big?
1879072121.name: Shell-breaker

1879072124.description: You have proven your mettle against the Orcs who have invaded northern Bree-land.
1879072124.name: Defender of Bree-land

1879072127.description: People may snicker, but how many of them have had to fight one of these giant bloodsuckers?
1879072127.name: Fly-swatter

1879072130.description: Spiders have become quite a threat of late in Bree-land, but your prowess against them is well known.
1879072130.name: Spider-foe

1879072133.description: The wights of the Barrow-downs no longer hold any terror for you. Now you just find them deeply unsettling.
1879072133.name: Bane of the Barrows

1879072136.description: Whence came these slimy horrors that now plague the Lone-lands, no one knows, but now you have taken their measure.
1879072136.name: Bog-hunter

1879072139.description: The Lords of the gaunt-men have taken notice of your activities....
1879072139.name: Enemy of the Dead

1879072142.description: No matter how many goblins you kill, the Lone-lands just seems to become overrun with yet more of them.
1879072142.name: Goblin-hewer

1879072145.description: Without your strength, it seems likely the Lone-lands would be overrun with Orcs by now.
1879072145.name: Champion of the Lone-lands

1879072148.description: The Lone-lands, too, are infested by these eight-legged horrors, each stronger than the last -- yet still they fall before you!
1879072148.name: Spider-bane

1879072151.description: Along with the goblins, Wargs have come to the Lone-lands. They'll not have free run as long as you stand against them!
1879072151.name: Warg-hunter

1879072155.description: The goblins have retaken deep delvings carved in the hills of the North Downs, inhabiting them in great droves. While they have learned to fear your name, you don't seem to have made much of a dent in their numbers.
1879072155.name: Cleaver of Goblins

1879072158.description: Most of the residents of the North Downs have been driven away by the orkish incursion, but those few who remain now herald your name as their saviour against these brutish invaders.
1879072158.name: Hero / Heroine of the North Downs

1879072161.description: Long ago many princes and warriors of the DÃºnedain fell upon the Fields of Fornost - you cannot say if these horrors are them, but either way you've returned many of them to the peace of the grave.
1879072161.name: Foe of Night

1879072164.description: Trolls -- they are among the strongest and perhaps the least intelligent of the servants of the Enemy. Now it seems that these inhuman giants wander the North Downs at will, or would, if you did not stand against them!
1879072164.name: Troll-hewer

1879072167.description: Anywhere goblins can be found, you'll likely encounter Wargs. Thanks to your valiant efforts there are fewer of them in the North Downs however.
1879072167.name: Warg-foe

1879072170.description: Legend has it that the Enemy spent long ages devising the great breed of Dragons that have bedeviled Middle-earth. Worms are among the lesser forms that were discarded along the way - but they are still deadly foes, and more common than their greater kin.
1879072170.name: Worm-slayer

1879072173.description: The bounders of the Shire look on you kindly for your help in dealing with the recent brigand troubles.
1879072173.name: Bounders-friend

1879072176.description: It has been long since the brood of Golfimbul endangered the folk of the Shire, but they will have to make it past you first.
1879072176.name: Protector of the Shire

1879072179.description: The harvest-flies are more of a threat to the crops than to the folk of the Shire, but the farmers are thankful for your efforts to exterminate them.
1879072179.name: Crop-saviour

1879072182.description: You're not sure that this was the title you were looking for when you set out on the path of an adventurer....
1879072182.name: Slug-squasher

1879072185.description: Like so many places in Middle-earth, the Shire has seen a recent infestation of dangerous spiders, but they have learned to fear your sting!
1879072185.name: Spider-sting

1879072188.description: Just as in olden days, wolves again threaten the Shire, but you have taught them a lesson they'll not soon forget.
1879072188.name: Fur-cutter

1879072191.description: The Dourhands have proven a sore thorn in the side of Durin's Folk, having lost the respect and trust of their kin.
1879072191.name: Defender of the Halls

1879072194.description: Ancestral foes of dwarf and Elf alike, goblins again challenge the lands of Ered Luin, but you stand ready to defy them.
1879072194.name: Guardian of Ered Luin

1879072197.description: Unlike the noble Eagles, the crooked hendrovail are used as spies for dark masters across many lands -- Ered Luin included.
1879072197.name: Feather-foe

1879072200.description: Spiders have long lurked in all the dark corners of Middle-earth, but those of Ered Luin, at least, have reason to fear you.
1879072200.name: Web-slasher

1879072203.description: Driven down from the frozen north, wolves are a constant challenge to all those who live in Ered Luin, but your prowess has proven their master.
1879072203.name: Wolf-tamer

1879072206.description: These evil Men wield terrible powers granted them by their Dark Lord -- but such magic will avail them not as you pursue them into the deepest corners of their great strongholds in the north.
1879072206.name: Doom of the Angmarim

1879072209.description: Numbering in the tens of thousands, Orcs have long formed the mainstay of the Enemy's armies. You long ago lost count of how many of these foul creatures have fallen before you - and yet their numbers seem undiminished.
1879072209.name: Bane of the Orcs

1879072212.description: The trolls of Angmar are the deadliest of all you have faced. Wielding arms and armour from the forges of the Enemy and possesed of a cruel cunning, even great heroes have fallen before their might.
1879072212.name: Bane of Trolls

1879072215.description: The mighty Uruk form the elite forces of the armies of Angmar. Having defeated so many of their kind in battle, your name now commands a certain respect - and even deeper enmity - among their ranks.
1879072215.name: Warlord of Angmar

1879072218.description: The dreadful Wargs raised within the kennels of Angmar have known no other masters - until now. Still, it seems they are not about to let you pet them.
1879072218.name: Lord / Lady of Fangs

1879072221.description: Angmar hosts a dread valley of spirits enthralled to the power of the Witch-King, and they do his bidding in his absence. There are few places in all Middle-Earth that inspire such dread as those halls - the Orcs and goblins give it wide breadth, while only the most fanatical of the Angmarim will enter to perform dark rites therein.
1879072221.name: Destiny of the Accursed

1879072224.description: Mishaphen half-children of the great Dragons of old, the Worms of Angmar possess a fair portion of their elder brood's power and cunning. Yet you have overcome their power and proven their match.
1879072224.name: Weird of the Worms

1879072228.description: You've heard that the giants sometimes breed the largest bears as pets - and that wouldn't surprise you. They grow them big here in the Misty Mountains - really big.
1879072228.name: Bear-wrestler

1879072231.description: You'd thought these great creatures must be legend and myth when you were told stories of them by your parents. Not any more. Their strength is as great as their size, and their bravery that of a creature that knows it is unmatched. Nevertheless, the valour of you and your companions has laid many of these titans low in battle.
1879072231.name: Bane of Titans

1879072234.description:
The Snow-beasts that inhabit the Misty Mountains are odd creatures. You'd only heard vague tales of them before you came there, and most people would consider them myths, but you've fought enough of them to be quite sure they are real.

Where they may have come from is anyone's guess. Perhaps the Enemy found them far in the distant North somewhere, beyond the boundaries of Man or Elf.
1879072234.name: Beast-hunter

1879072237.description: As if the biting cold in the Misty Mountains wasn't bad enough, it seems to have given rise to a particularly unpleasant breed of troll. These creatures thrive in the ice and frost, and they lurk here waiting to crush and devour any traveller unlucky enough to stumble upon them.
1879072237.name: Vanquisher of Trolls

1879072240.description: Where there are goblins there are Wargs, and the Misty Mountains are no exception. Tempered by the deadly cold and harsh conditions, these Wargs have become particularly vicious and deadly but you've found them to be passable opponents at best.
1879072240.name: Warg-hunter

1879072243.description: It is said that worms have long lived in the far north, among the desolate and frozen wastes. Alas, it seems only natural then that as the gates of Angmar have been laid open that they should have unleashed many of the creatures into the frozen peaks of the Misty Mountains, there to breed and to terrorize any who attempt the dangerous passage.
1879072243.name: Worm-bane

1879072247.description: And here you'd thought nothing could be worse than the bugs in Midgewater. These many legged horrors have changed your mind on the matter, but not stopped your battle to protect Middle-earth.
1879072247.name: Chitin-smasher

1879072250.description: It took more than a flyswatter to bring down so many of these prodigious foes - a feat for which you are rightly renowned.
1879072250.name: Giant-slayer

1879072253.description: These lands weren't named the Trollshaws without good reason. You've certainly found no shortage of the brutes to test your mettle against!
1879072253.name: Troll-slayer

1879072256.description: Even the Elves of Rivendell claim not to know whence the horrid wights infesting the Trollshaws came. Nevertheless you have forced many of them back into the earth from which they escaped.
1879072256.name: the Purifier

1879072259.description: The wolves that inhabit the Trollshaws are among the most wild and powerful of that breed. Serving neither Man nor Goblin, these wolves prey upon any foolish enough to venture into their territory - save for you.
1879072259.name: Tail-cleaver

1879072262.description: Where could so many of these terrible beasts have been hidden away? The wastes of the far North, or buried beneath the Gates of Angmar? It doesn't really matter where they came from, so long as you strive to drive them from the lands of Middle-earth.
1879072262.name: Worm-carver

1879073639.description: You grew up in Bree-land, once part of the North Kingdom of Arnor, once ruled by Elendil the Tall as High King of Middle-earth, and later by his elder son Isildur. Now it is but a simple, rustic land, and the North Kingdom is no more.
1879073639.name: of Bree-land

1879073640.description: You come from the Dale-lands in the north-east of Middle-earth, beneath the Lonely Mountain, where Bard the Bowman slew the dragon Smaug and fought in the Battle of Five Armies.
1879073640.name: of Dale

1879073641.description: You hail from the land of Gondor, the South Kingdom once ruled conjointly by the sons of Elendil, Isildur and AnÃ¡rion, ever-watchful against the looming threat of Mordor.
1879073641.name: of Gondor

1879073642.description: You are one of the Horse-lords of the Riddermark, the realm granted to Eorl the Young by Cirion, Steward of Gondor, currently ruled by ThÃ©oden, son of Thengel.
1879073642.name: of Rohan

1879073643.description: Lovers of trees and woodlands, the Fallohides were the first hobbits to come to the Shire. They generally tend to be fairer of skin and hair, as well as taller and more slender.
1879073643.name: of the Fallohides

1879073644.description: The Harfoots are the most prodigious hole-dwellers and were the first to cross west into Eriador. They generally tend to be browner of skin than the other kindreds, as well as smaller and shorter.
1879073644.name: of the Harfoots

1879073645.description: The Stoors were the last of the hobbit kindreds to come to the Shire, settling at last in the eastern marshlands of the Shire. They generally tend to be heavier and broader of build than the other kindreds.
1879073645.name: of the Stoors

1879073646.description: You come from the Iron Hills, settled by dwarves as a refuge from the Cold-drakes, and whence came DÃ¡in Ironfoot, King under the Mountain, kinsman of the great Thorin Oakenshield.
1879073646.name: of the Iron Hills

1879073647.description: You hail from Erebor, the Lonely Mountain, where Smaug the Golden made his lair until Thorin Oakenshield reclaimed it for his people. There does DÃ¡in Ironfoot now rule as King under the Mountain.
1879073647.name: of the Lonely Mountain

1879073648.description: Your home is in Ered Luin, the Blue Mountains, where there had once been two great dwarf-kingdoms and where the kinsmen of ThrÃ¡in and his son Thorin Oakenshield lived in exile after Smaug drove them from the Lonely Mountain.
1879073648.name: of the Blue Mountains

1879073649.description: You are from Ered Mithrin, the Grey Mountains, the chief of which is Mount Gundabad, from whence came Durin the Deathless, first Father of the Dwarves. Your kindred returned to the Mountains after the Dragons perished.
1879073649.name: of the Grey Mountains

1879073650.description: You are from the south-western halls of Ered Nimrais, the White Mountains in the south bordering the lands of Andrast. Though your kingdom lies far from the central mountains where Men once dwelt, the rumour of the Oathbreakers has given your realm an ill name.
1879073650.name: of the White Mountains

1879073651.description: You hail from Lindon, the green lands of the Elves between Ered Luin and the Sea, where Gil-galad, the last great Elf-king, once ruled. CÃ­rdan the Shipwright now rules there from Mithlond, the Grey Havens.
1879073651.name: of Lindon

1879073652.description: You come from LothlÃ³rien, the fabled golden woods whose Elves dwell high in the mallorn-trees and are ruled by Celeborn, wisest of the Eldar of Middle-earth, and the Lady Galadriel.
1879073652.name: of LÃ³rien

1879073653.description: You are a Wood-elf of Mirkwood, once called Greenwood the Great, where King Thranduil keeps watch against the growing darkness of Dol Guldur, former stronghold of Sauron in his guise as the Necromancer.
1879073653.name: of Mirkwood

1879073654.description: You hail from Imladris, called Rivendell by Men, built by Elrond Halfelven as a refuge for the Elves of Eregion as they fled destruction at the hands of Sauron.
1879073654.name: of Rivendell

1879073655.description: You are of the Nandor of Edhellond, the great Elf-haven in the south built by Amroth at the Mouths of Anduin.

1879074197.name: Chief

1879074198.description: You are an officer within a Kinship.
1879074198.name: Voluntary Assistant Chief

1879074199.description: You are a member within a Kinship.
1879074199.name: Kinswoman / Kinsman

1879077125.description: Mordirith, leader of Angmar in the stead of the Witch-king, looks upon you as a trusted servant. His favour will earn you greater favour with the Lugburz!
1879077125.name: Favoured of Mordirith

1879077131.description: You have defeated the captains of Ringdyr.
1879077131.name: Conqueror of Ringdyr

1879077133.description: You have defeated the captains of Tol Ascarnen.
1879077133.name: Conqueror of Tol Ascarnen

1879077135.description: You have defeated the captains of the Towers.
1879077135.name: Conqueror of the Towers

1879077137.description: You've hunted down a number of these annoying little backstabbers and shown them what it means to oppose the will of Angmar.
1879077137.name: Snitch-killer

1879077139.description: Those who would steal from the lords of Angmar will die by the sword, and at your hands many of them have.
1879077139.name: Thief-slayer

1879077141.description: Never trust a thief. For that matter, don't trust anyone.
1879077141.name: Burglar-basher

1879077143.description: Burglars can run, but they cannot hide from you. You've killed a great many of these filthy little sneaks in your time.
1879077143.name: Bane of Shadows

1879077145.description: Tricksy and false? Hah! You've seen how 'tricksy' Burglars are when they are writhing in pain as you prepare to strike the killing blow. It's hardly even a sporting challenge any more.
1879077145.name: Trickster's Scourge

1879077147.description: These fools would lead the forces of Men? Then let them lead from the grave!
1879077147.name: Captain's Foe

1879077149.description: Rally their allies to them as they might, you've cut through and killed many of these banner-waving cretins.
1879077149.name: Captain-slayer

1879077151.description: The banners make them easy to spot on the battlefield, and ripe for the killing as you and your hordes fall upon them from the darkness.
1879077151.name: Banner-shredder

1879077153.description: Without their leaders, the forces of Men often fall to panic and cowardly flight. You have excelled at extinguishing these little sparks of false 'hope' upon the field of battle.
1879077153.name: Bane of Order

1879077155.description:
Few things warm your dark heart quite like the crestfallen look upon the faces of your enemies as yet another of their Lords falls in battle before you.

It is a sight you have enjoyed so very often...
1879077155.name: Defiler of Lords

1879077157.description: These self-righteous crusaders have often fallen before your own unheralded strength.
1879077157.name: Champion's Foe

1879077159.description: Champions respect strength above all else - a trait which you have displayed in plenty as you've hewed through their ranks.
1879077159.name: Slayer of Champions

1879077161.description:
He who lives by the sword had best expect to die by it.

You make a point of giving these fool Champions every opportunity to do so at your hands.
1879077161.name: Sword-breaker

1879077163.description:
What good is courage to one who lies, broken and bleeding beneath your feet? Who knows?

Who cares.
1879077163.name: Bane of Courage

1879077165.description: Hah! For self-styled 'Heroes', these Champions fall like wheat before the scythe of your power. They are no match for you, nor shall they ever be!
1879077165.name: Doom of Heroes

1879077167.description:
These self-styled Guardians stand between you and the towns and villages of the West, which lie ripe for the plucking.

The more of them you kill, the sooner you can start the looting.
1879077167.name: Guardian-killer

1879077169.description: Why would these iron-hided scum stand between you and the weak? You'll never understand it - but you've proven they can be swept aside all the same.
1879077169.name: Sentinel-slayer

1879077171.description: Though they carry great shields and clothe themselves in burnished steel, no-one may stand before the power of Angmar and live. You've seen to that.
1879077171.name: Shield-breaker

1879077173.description:
Defenders of the Weak indeed! Who then shall defend these supposed Guardians from you, eh?

No-one, that's who...
1879077173.name: Guardian's Bane

1879077175.description:
Those who stand before the tide are doomed to drown in its fury.

You charge in the vanguard of the endless armies of Angmar and crush those Guardians who dare to stand with armies of the West, without mercy or hesitation.
1879077175.name: Doom of the Stalwart

1879077177.description: These vicious opponents would attempt to sap the strength of Angmar from afar, you've found it best to take the battle to them in person.
1879077177.name: Hunter-killer

1879077179.description: You've killed your share of the enemy's scouts. They would do better to cower behind their allies in battle, but then what's the sport in that?
1879077179.name: Scout-blinder

1879077181.description: With neither shield or armour, Hunters make for easy prey upon the battlefield. Sure the arrows sting a bit, but pain is the mark of a true warrior.
1879077181.name: Bow-cleaver

1879077183.description: Ah, the joy when the tables are turned and the Hunter becomes the Hunted! So many of these miscreants have fallen before you now that you've nearly lost count.
1879077183.name: Hunter's Bane

1879077185.description: Bows may be fearsome weapons in skilled hands, but they cannot protect their wielders from the swift and certain death that you bring upon them in battle. They are just more kindling for the bonfires of Angmar!
1879077185.name: Doom of the Archer

1879077187.description: The Wise? feh! The truly Wise need understand only power. Those who profess wisdom in knowledge often die at your hands.
1879077187.name: Lore-master's Foe

1879077189.description: No magic can protect these bookworms from your wrath. If they understood even a fraction of the power commanded by the Lords of Angmar, they would cower in abject surrender before death.
1879077189.name: Sage-slayer

1879077191.description: What's so special about a staff? Just another stick to be broken - right before you break the one who wields it, as you have so often before.
1879077191.name: Staff-breaker

1879077193.description: What good are old books and a fine pointy hat when you've got three feet of steel protruding from your gut? None at all! You've proved the wisdom of that statement often enough.
1879077193.name: Bane of the Wise

1879077195.description:
No overblown scribe can challenge you on the battlefield.

Scrolls, books, staves, robes - all shall burn in the bonfires of Angmar!
1879077195.name: Scourge of the Learned

1879077197.description:
What kind of fool comes to the battlefield to sing rather than fight?

A dead fool.
1879077197.name: Minstrel's Foe

1879077199.description: The songs of the West sound far more pleasing to your ears when they gurgle forth from a slit throat.
1879077199.name: Bard-slayer

1879077201.description: The discordant snapping of strings, the splintering of wood, and the screams of the dying are all the music needed to accompany your rampage.
1879077201.name: Harp-cutter

1879077203.description:
The leaderless scum of the West are said to believe that the world was born from a song.

Perhaps, perhaps not, but the last music they shall hear before their fall shall be the war-drums of Angmar!
1879077203.name: Troubador's Bane

1879077205.description:
In the wake of your passage, the fields of battle take on an unnatural stillness broken only by the moans of the dying.

No songs escape from the lips of the fallen, for no life remains to utter them.
1879077205.name: Silencer of Songs

1879082937.description: You have assisted Gundzor earning the rank of drudge.
1879082937.name: Gundzor's Drudge

1879082940.description: You have continued to assist Gundzor earning the rank of flunky.
1879082940.name: Gundzor's Flunky

1879082943.description: You have become known to Gundzor as more than a servant; you are a defender of his post in the Grimwood.
1879082943.name: Gundzor's Fist

1879082946.description: You have assisted BÃ»rzgoth and earned the title of his thrall.
1879082946.name: BÃ»rzgoth's Thrall

1879082949.description: You have continued to assist BÃ»rzgoth and earned the right to be his toady.
1879082949.name: BÃ»rzgoth's Toady

1879082952.description: You have become known to BÃ»rzgoth as one who will do as he says, when he says.
1879082952.name: BÃ»rzgoth's Bootlicker

1879082955.description: You have assisted the master of Lugazag and earned the right to be at his beck and call.
1879082955.name: Tharbil's Minion

1879082958.description: You have continued to assist the master of Lugazag and firmed your position as his servant.
1879082958.name: Tharbil's Lackey

1879082961.description: You have become known to Tharbil as more than a servant; you are a defender of his post at Lugazag.
1879082961.name: Tharbil's Whip

1879082964.description: You have assisted the master of Tirith Rhaw and earned station as his servant.
1879082964.name: Servant to Barashish

1879082967.description: You have earned greater favour of the master of Tirith Rhaw and can now be named a hound. A loyal dog.
1879082967.name: Hound to Barashish

1879082970.description: You have become known to Barashish as more than a servant; you are a defender of his post at Tirith Rhaw.
1879082970.name: Blade of Barashish

1879082973.description: You have assisted the master of Tol Ascarnen and earned the right to be called a truckler.
1879082973.name: TrintrÃ» Truckler

1879082976.description: You have continued to assist TrintrÃ» earning the right to be called his lickspittle.
1879082976.name: TrintrÃ»'s Lickspittle

1879082979.description: None question your devotion to TrintrÃ», thus you are called his sycophant.
1879082979.name: TrintrÃ»'s Sycophant

1879083984.description: Helping Holly Hornblower has honoured her and hastened hungry hobbits into happy hobbits.
1879083984.name: Pie-runner

1879083985.description: For your help to the Quick Post, Postmaster Proudfoot has declared you an official postman.
1879083985.name: of the Quick Post

1879083996.description: With your coming sounds the trump of Doom, for by your hand have many of the warriors of the Free Peoples fallen bested by your might.
1879083996.name: Hand of Doom

1879083997.description: Your legend has grown so much amongst the Elves that you are now a true villain. They know only to run from you when you near them!
1879083997.name: Elf-slayer

1879083998.description: Valour crumbles when you near. The dwarves' courage spills from them as easily as their innards when you are about. The death delivered by your hands sunders hope.
1879083998.name: Enemy of Valour

1879083999.description: Men quake at the mention of your name, as your blade bites deeply into their flesh.
1879083999.name: Man-foe

1879084000.description: Your continued destruction of the little folk drives a spike of fear into their hearts.
1879084000.name: Hobbit-bane

1879084001.description: Light ebbs in your presence. Strength leaves the enemy as the darkness you bring clouds their hope and drives dread into their hearts.
1879084001.name: Slayer of Light

1879084002.description: Your name is known amongst the Elves. It is used to strike fear into the hearts of the young.
1879084002.name: Elf-bane

1879084003.description: When Angmar's Army moves beneath the world to face the dwarves in their mountain homes, perhaps you shall be the one to lead it. You have proven yourself most adept at slaying these vermin!
1879084003.name: Scourge of the Undermountain

1879084004.description: You are an officer within a Tribe.
1879084004.name: War-boss

1879084005.description: Without compassion or care you flay flesh from the little folk and have become one of the most adept at culling their number from the world.
1879084005.name: Hobbit-slayer

1879084006.description: You are the founder of a Tribe.
1879084006.name: Bone-speaker

1879084007.description: You are a herald of the Dark Lord. You have culled countless numbers from the field of battle and none escape your grasp.
1879084007.name: Herald of Darkness

1879084008.description: Dwarves quake before you! You cleave and heave their bodies aside by the hundred!
1879084008.name: Dwarf-tosser

1879084009.description: You are a leader within a Tribe.
1879084009.name: Chieftain

1879084010.description: You are the founder of a Tribe.
1879084010.name: Warlord

1879084011.description: You are known as the Bane of the West, for none of their warriors can stand against you, and windrows of their fallen lie heaped in your wake.
1879084011.name: Bane of the West

1879084012.description: Continued efforts against the dwarves earn you great glory. You are seen as their bane by others in Angmar's ranks.
1879084012.name: Dwarf-bane

1879084013.description: You are an officer within a Tribe.
1879084013.name: Field-master

1879084014.description: Slaughtering the little folk has earned you a mark of savagery against their kind.
1879084014.name: Hobbit-foe

1879084015.description: You are an officer within a Tribe.
1879084015.name: Sentinel

1879084016.description: Your victories against the bearded folk beneath the mountain brand you their foe.
1879084016.name: Dwarf-foe

1879084017.description: Countless deaths by your hand tarnish Men. Their honour breaks as easily as their wills when you stride onto the fields of battle.
1879084017.name: Enemy of Honour

1879084018.description: Men fear you. There are none who do not know your name in battle and all Men quake in terror at its mention.
1879084018.name: Scourge of Man

1879084019.description: Your blade has tasted the flesh of many Elves and it desires the blood of more.
1879084019.name: Elf-foe

1879084020.description: You are a leader within a Tribe.
1879084020.name: Warrior

1879084021.description: Cleaving through the ranks of Men drives you to near frenzy. You are known for slaughter and tearing flesh from Men.
1879084021.name: Man-flayer

1879084022.description: You are a grunt within a Tribe.
1879084022.name: Grunt

1879084023.description: You are a grunt within a Tribe.
1879084023.name: Grunt

1879084024.description: You are known as a tormenter of the Free Peoples.
1879084024.name: Tormenter

1879084025.description: Your blade drinks the blood of Man freely. There are few who would stand against you!
1879084025.name: Man-slayer

1879084026.description: Your rank, name, and surname, sans title.

1879084027.description: You are a leader within a Tribe.
1879084027.name: Battle-master

1879084028.description: You are the founder of a Tribe.
1879084028.name: Ancestor

1879084029.description: You are a leader within a Tribe.
1879084029.name: Warmonger

1879084030.description: You are a grunt within a Tribe.
1879084030.name: Grunt

1879084032.description: You are an officer within a Tribe.
1879084032.name: Watcher

1879084033.description: The field of battle serves as a garden from which you reap the heads of the fallen. You are a true harvester of sorrow.
1879084033.name: Harvester of Sorrow

1879084034.description: Grace falters when you draw close. There are none amongst the Elves who will stand before you. The destruction wrought by your hand has crippled grace.
1879084034.name: Enemy of Grace

1879084035.description: There are no little folk who dare stand before you. Your prowess over them is known to all as you tear through them with impunity.
1879084035.name: Scourge of the Little Folk

1879084036.description: You are the founder of a Tribe.
1879084036.name: Overseer

1879084037.description: You are a grunt within a Tribe.
1879084037.name: Grunt

1879084038.description: Angmar casts a favouring eye upon you, you are known as an elite amongst their number. A hound of Mordirith; a Black Dog!
1879084038.name: Black Dog

1879084039.description: All who draw breath and hold ties to the Elven Folk fear your blade. You drive their number from the fields of battle.
1879084039.name: Scourge of the Fair Folk

1879084040.description: Your domination over the little folk is absolute. The blood spilled by your hands has soiled the innocence these creatures once enjoyed.
1879084040.name: Enemy of Innocence

1879084408.description: You are now indoctrinated to Angmar's Army!
1879084408.name: Servant of Angmar

1879086560.description: You have completed part one of the first volume of the Shadows of Angmar.
1879086560.name: a Light from the Shadow

1879087032.description: You have slain a great many of the tomb-robbers that threaten the burial places of the Kings of AnnÃºminas.
1879087032.name: Tomb-warden

1879087033.description: Some secret lies hidden within the glimmering lights that haunt the fields of Evendim -- it seems on the tip of your tongue, but ever eludes youâ€¦.
1879087033.name: Keeper of Mysteries

1879087034.description: The savage Gauredain have learned to respect your strength, and perhaps even fear you -- if they ever allowed themselves to show fear in battle.
1879087034.name: Slayer of the Gauredain

1879087035.description: The Stone-giants inhabiting the hills above Evendim have come to call you their foe, and they plan for the day when they might have their vengeance upon you.
1879087035.name: Enemy of the Giants

1879087036.description: The goblins and the strange little boggarts that creep about the fringes of Evendim have learned to give you wide berth if they value their lives at all.
1879087036.name: Goblin-foe

1879087037.description:
Thus far you have laid waste to the deadly Kergrim and have not yet fallen prey to their vicious claws.

Should the day come when you make a mistake in battle against them, not even your bones will be left for others to mourn.
1879087037.name: Bane of the Kergrim

1879087038.description: The salamanders of Evendim have tried time and again to destroy you, to no avail as their fire flickers and dims before your might.
1879087038.name: Quencher of Flames

1879088050.description: For completing the Inn League's grueling test, you are now a true member.
1879088050.name: Inn League Member

1879088137.description: For winning a Hobnanigans match as a member of the Flying Feathers team.
1879088137.name: Flying Feathers Champion

1879088138.description: For winning a Hobnanigans match as a member of the Steel Beaks team.
1879088138.name: Chicken Chaser

1879088665.description: Even the reborn dragon Thorog has fallen before you.
1879088665.name: Doom of Thorog Reborn

1879088666.description: Many worked together to bring this victory, but you stand above the rest, a true hero.
1879088666.name: Reclaimer of MÃ­rdanant

1879088667.description: The Servants Three are no more, but you prevail.
1879088667.name: Slayer of the Servants Three

1879088668.description: The Corcur of Helegrod know your name, but speak it in frightened whispers.
1879088668.name: Enemy of the Corcur

1879088669.description: Angmar now fears your name and the names of your allies.
1879088669.name: Enemy of Angmar

1879088670.description: You have harvested the evil venom of Zaudru's brood to serve the greater good.
1879088670.name: the Venomous

1879088671.description: Many of the brood of Zaudru have fallen to your might.
1879088671.name: Hated by Zaudru

1879088672.description: Not even the foul Zaudru can stand before you.
1879088672.name: Dispatcher of Zaudru

1879088673.description: StorvÃ¢gÃ»n's treachery, and his life, have been ended.
1879088673.name: StorvÃ¢gÃ»n's End

1879088674.description: Those who sold their loyalty for riches have tasted the vengeance of the righteous.
1879088674.name: Giant Dues-collector

1879088675.description: Less ice-hatchlings now and less drakes later, a victory for the Free Peoples!
1879088675.name: Hatchery Raider

1879088676.description: Being a true hero requires more than strength of arms and will.
1879088676.name: the Selfless

1879093986.description: Amongst the rotting horror of Haudh Iarchith, a gathering of corrupt and evil entities holds sway over a dark court - or at least, they did, before you found and destroyed them.
1879093986.name: Executioner of the Wicked

1879093987.description: Many fallen spirits roam the dark tunnels of Haudh Iarchith, yet if there is anything that they might fear amongst the living, it is you.
1879093987.name: Nemesis of the Fallen

1879093988.description: The evil spider Gwigon has made its lair amongst the twisting barrow of Haudh Iarchith and there his brood multiplies, save for your efforts to exterminate them.
1879093988.name: Brood-hunter

1879093989.description: So many corpses have clawed up from their graves amongst the labyrinthine barrows of Haudh Iarchith, that it seems you have more need of a shovel than a sword.
1879093989.name: Grave-digger

1879093990.description:
A number of vicious and corrupt beasts reside within the ruins of SarnÃºr, and they have fallen under the sway of the Dourhands and their allies.

Your will and strength has mastered these vermin nevertheless.
1879093990.name: Master of Beasts

1879093991.description: The Dourhand brigands have established a stronghold within the ancient ruins of SarnÃºr, but your battles against them have thinned their numbers and weakened their hold on it.
1879093991.name: Betrayer's Bane

1879093992.description: An alliance of enemies plots against Ered Luin from within the ancient ruins of SarnÃºr, as the traitorous Dourhand seek to bring an array of forces to bear against their hated cousins the Longbeards - luckily, your excursions into the ruins have resulted in the deaths of many of their leaders.
1879093992.name: Avenger of SarnÃºr

1879093993.description:
It seems that the trolls inhabiting SarnÃºr are of a particularly dim-witted - if brutal - strain.

Under the guidance of the Dourhands however, they cannot be ignored - though how long their allegiance might last is uncertainâ€¦
1879093993.name: Troll-kicker

1879094070.description: You ate the cheese even after observing all of the warning signs. This makes you especially unwise.
1879094070.name: The Unwise

1879094073.description: Let it be known to all Men, Elves, dwarves, and hobbits (hereinafter 'the Free Peoples') that Will Tuffin, being of suitable age and discretion and found within the boundaries of the Shire, has been served with process in accordance with applicable law and with all due diligence by the bearer of this title. The complainant, Hob Hillbrow, seeks reasonably foreseeable damages as well as exemplary damages, if it please the Court. Respectfully submitted by a servant of process in the case.
1879094073.name: Servant of Process

1879094074.description: There are many deep secrets in Middle Earth, but you have great insight into what part the chickens play in it all.
1879094074.name: Crosser of Roads

1879098910.description: You have proven yourself to be a friend of the creatures of the wild.
1879098910.name: Friend of the Wild

1879099327.description: These winged villains are little more than pests, but if it is true that they do indeed spy for the dark powers, then it is best that you have rid the Lone-lands of so many of them.
1879099327.name: Wing-cutter

1879099328.description: One more victory for you and your allies - one less troll to worry about later.
1879099328.name: Troll-beater

1879101828.description: You have passed on your knowledge of music and song to others who shall carry on the tradition.
1879101828.name: Mentor of Song

1879101829.description: You have been a particularly diligent mentor to those who would learn of music and song, and have spread your knowledge to many students.
1879101829.name: Exemplar of Song

1879101834.description: With the aid of your brave fellows and the High Elf GlathlÃ­rel, you have destroyed the dread Balrog Thaurlach!
1879101834.name: Vanquisher of Thaurlach

1879101835.description: Yours was the hand to take up Thaurlach's shattered chain, and bear it forth into the light as proof of your company's great deeds.
1879101835.name: Lord / Lady of the Shattered Chain

1879101836.description: The Orc-chieftain ThrÃ¢ng has fallen before the bravery and skill of you and your fellows, bringing you one step closer to destroying his dark master.
1879101836.name: Ruination of ThrÃ¢ng

1879101837.description: Your battles within the rift have aided the Eldgang Giants, who continue to struggle against the powers of darkness even in this terrible place.
1879101837.name: Saviour of the Eldgang

1879101993.description: You have completed part two of the first volume of the Shadows of Angmar.
1879101993.name: Bearer of Hope

1879103022.description: You have skilfully matched wits with a Riddle-master and solved the most puzzling of riddles!
1879103022.name: Fathomer of Riddles

1879103695.description: You are strongly aware that you only get one chance to make a first impression, and take great care to ensure that your garments are up to the task!
1879103695.name: the Fashionable

1879103696.description: You do care about appearances, but your look would benefit from a little more time spent on simple coordination.
1879103696.name: the Unfashionable

1879103697.description: Your choices strongly suggest that you set out to insult the entire Tailoring profession and all those who hold it dear.  If you're trying to make a statement, you certainly have!
1879103697.name: the Eye-sore

1879104190.description: You have done great work in aiding Nethraw in his study of Rhudarian History.
1879104190.name: Sage of Rhudaur

1879106623.description: You are a Supreme Master Cook.
1879106623.name: Supreme Master Cook

1879106625.description: You are a Supreme Master Scholar.
1879106625.name: Supreme Master Scholar

1879106628.description: You are a Supreme Master Tailor.
1879106628.name: Supreme Master Tailor

1879106630.description: You are a Supreme Master Jeweller.
1879106630.name: Supreme Master Jeweller

1879106635.description: You are a Supreme Master Metalsmith.
1879106635.name: Supreme Master Metalsmith

1879106638.description: You are a Supreme Master Farmer.
1879106638.name: Supreme Master Farmer

1879106648.description: You are a Supreme Master Prospector.
1879106648.name: Supreme Master Prospector

1879106651.description: You are a Supreme Master Forester.
1879106651.name: Supreme Master Forester

1879106654.description: You are a Supreme Master Woodworker.
1879106654.name: Supreme Master Woodworker

1879106657.description: You are a Supreme Master Weaponsmith.
1879106657.name: Supreme Master Weaponsmith

1879107443.description: For helping the Inn League members with their tasks, you have been promoted to Notable status. With great pride will you wear this title among the people.
1879107443.name: Inn League Notable

1879107444.description: For helping the Inn League members with their tasks, you have been promoted to Senior Member status.
1879107444.name: Inn League Senior Member

1879107446.description: After consuming spirits from around Eriador, you are now a sage of the Inn League.
1879107446.name: Inn League Sage of Fine Spirits

1879107698.description: Against all odds, you have proven triumphant in a great test of skill and wit!
1879107698.name: the Triumphant

1879107699.description: There are few paths in Middle-earth that you have not trod.
1879107699.name: Worldly Traveller

1879107700.description: You are always quick with a smile and a warm hello!
1879107700.name: Greeter of Kin

1879107701.description: Your loyalty is second to none.
1879107701.name: the Loyal

1879107702.description: Your selfless actions for others have not gone unnoticed!
1879107702.name: Pillar of the Community
